1] What is Volatile , How it resolves visibilty problem?

 ⚙ CPU cache structure :

    - Cpu with two core
    - each core has local cache & one common shared cache
    - Visibility Problem :
        - If one thread modify the flag value it will  refelects only in local cache
        - when you used volatile keyword it flush  the local cache changes to shared cache and refresh the other
          core cache flag value where other threads are running
    - EX : volatile boolean flag=false;


2] Synchronization Problem:

  - Two thread reading value at the same time & output is not as expected ( Example: value++)
  - Solution 1 :  With synchronized block

        synchronized(obj){
        value++;
        }

  - Solution 2 : With AtomicInteger

          AtomicInteger value =new AtomicInteger(1);

          value.increment();
     - method :  incrementAndGet | decrementAndGet | addAndGet(int delta) | compareAndSet( int expectVal,int newVal)


