4] Difference between Concurrency vs Parallelism

   - blog : https://www.baeldung.com/cs/concurrency-vs-parallelism

   ⚙ Scheduler : Responsible for scheduling the thread on to the cpu Core


   ⚙ Parallelism : Is about doing lot of things at once

        -Tools to enable Parallelism:

           - Threads
           - ThreadPool
               - ExcecutorService
               - ForkJoinPool
               - Custom ThreadPools (eg:  Web Servers)

           - Requires  > 1 CPU cores

   ⚙ Concurrency : Is about dealing lot of things at once

      - shared resource is to be accessed/updated
      - multiple tasks need to be coordinated

      -Tools to enable Parallelism:

         - Locks/Synchronized
         - Atomic Classes
         - Concurrent DataStructure ( eg: ConcurrentHashMap, BlockingQueue)
         - CompletableFuture
         - CountdownLatch / Phaser / CyclicBarrier / Semaphore etc.

